ed the generated tests and test-only wiring that caused those non-metadata failures and did not modify metadata files as part of this intervention.\\n\\n## Failure root causes and intervention\\n\\n- `JdbcUtilsAnonymous1Test.fallsBackToObjectInputStreamWhenContextClassLoaderRejectsSerializedClass()` was the failure in the provided Gradle excerpt. The native-image JUnit launcher could not resolve its unique ID, and the test depends on `SysProperties.USE_THREAD_CONTEXT_CLASS_LOADER` and a rejecting context class loader. This is image-initialization/class-loader behavior, not missing reachability metadata, so `JdbcUtilsAnonymous1Test.java` was removed.\\n- `SourceCompilerTest.compilesWithJavaxToolsCompilerAndDiscoversStaticMethod()` and `SourceCompilerTest.compilesWithLegacySunJavacAndDiscoversStaticMethod()` failed in the metadata-fix log while compiling and loading new `h2.generated.*` classes at native-image runtime. Runtime source compilation and loading newly generated bytecode is not expressible as repository reachability metadata, so `SourceCompilerTest.java` was removed.\\n- `TriggerObjectTest.compilesTriggerSourceAndInvokesFactoryMethod()` exercised H2 trigger source compilation into a dynamic class. This has the same runtime-source-compilation limitation, so only that generated method and its `SourceTrigger` fixture were removed. The trigger-class registration test remains.\\n- `UpgradeTest.loadsAndUnloadsLegacyDriverWithUpgradeTool()` used a test-only legacy H2 jar and dynamic driver loading/unloading. The log showed this path destabilized the active H2 driver and caused downstream JDBC failures, which is test behavior rather than a metadata gap. `UpgradeTest.java`, the legacy-H2 dependency/resource copy, and the `h2-upgrade/legacy-h2.jar` resource include were removed.\\n- `MemoryUnmapperTest.unmapUsesLegacyCleanerFallbackWhenUnsafeIsUnavailable()` used a custom `URLClassLoader` to reload H2 classes while hiding `sun.misc.Unsafe`. That loader-isolation behavior is not reliable in the native image, so only that generated fallback test and its test-only loader/service fixtures were removed. The direct and heap buffer `MemoryUnmapper` coverage remains.\\n- A rerun exposed a generated test-only native-image option `-H:Preserve=package=java.sql` that failed image building because the package request could not be matched for one of the preserved paths. This was a native-image option/test-harness issue, not metadata, so that build argument was removed.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\nAfter the intervention, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.h2database:h2:2.1.210 --stacktrace` passed. The native test run reported `32 tests successful` and `0 tests failed`.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining H2 support still exercises valid reachability-metadata coverage: JDBC use, serialization/deserialization, resources, configured reflection helpers, ICU collation, file-system wrappers, authentication XML parsing, trigger class loading, user aggregates, object conversion, and direct H2 database operations. Those paths are normal library behavior that can be supported by reachability metadata, and the passing native run confirms the preserved generated support is useful once the non-metadata-only tests are removed.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_9\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/zsh -lc 'cat stats/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/stats.json'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_9\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/zsh -lc 'cat stats/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/stats.json'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"{\\n  \\\"versions\\\" : [ {\\n    \\\"version\\\" : \\\"2.1.210\\\",\\n    \\\"dynamicAccess\\\" : {\\n      \\\"breakdown\\\" : {\\n        \\\"reflection\\\" : {\\n          \\\"coverageRatio\\\" : 0.113402,\