ctor-j/8.0.31/stats.json:14:          \\\"totalCalls\\\" : 4\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/com.mysql/mysql-connector-j/8.0.31/stats.json:17:      \\\"coverageRatio\\\" : 0.280702,\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/com.mysql/mysql-connector-j/8.0.31/stats.json:18:      \\\"coveredCalls\\\" : 16,\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/com.mysql/mysql-connector-j/8.0.31/stats.json:19:      \\\"totalCalls\\\" : 57\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/com.mysema.commons/mysema-commons-lang/0.2.4/stats.json:6:      \\\"coverageRatio\\\" : 1.0,\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/com.mysema.commons/mysema-commons-lang/0.2.4/stats.json:7:      \\\"coveredCalls\\\" : 0,\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/com.mysema.commons/mysema-commons-lang/0.2.4/stats.json:8:      \\\"totalCalls\\\" : 0\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:20:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Iterative add-new-library workflow guided by dynamic-access coverage.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:24:    REQUIRED_PROMPTS = [\\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\"]\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:49:            \\\"dynamic-access\\\",\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:50:            \\\"dynamic-access-coverage.json\\\",\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:154:                    \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\",\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:160:                self._print_dynamic_access_detail(\\\"agent: running dynamic-access prompt\\\", indent_level=2)\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:223:                        \\\"result: dynamic-access report unavailable after test run\\\",\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:271:                        f\\\"Partial dynamic-access coverage for {class_name} \\\"\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:496:                \\\"Coverage report loaded but contains no usable dynamic-access guidance:\\\",\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:500:                \\\"cause=no_dynamic_access hasDynamicAccess={has_dynamic_access} totalCalls={total_calls} \\\"\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:501:                \\\"coveredCalls={covered_calls} classes={class_count}\\\".format(\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:572:        log_stage(\\\"dynamic-access\\\", message)\\n../3992-53219949/forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:576:        log_stage(\\\"dynamic-access\\\", message, indent_level=indent_level)\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-java-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR described as `fixes-java-run-fail` or one that fixes Java/JVM runtime test failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the Java runtime fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair tests, dependencies, or narrow runtime setup after an existing library version compiles, but the JVM-based test fails when it runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to restore Java runtime behavior for the new version while preserving meaningful test and dynamic-access coverage.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:21:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:60:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:61:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:71:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/runtime-surface change.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/software.amazon.awssdk/s3/2.25.3/execution-metrics.json:35:        \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 1.0,\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/software.amazon.awssdk/s3/2.25.3/execution-metrics.json:36:        \\\"coveredCalls\\\": 0,\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/software.amazon.awssdk/s3/2.25.3/execution-metrics.json:37:        \\\"totalCalls\\\": 0\\n../2860-7c284b20/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\\n../2860-7c284b20/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\\n../2860-7c284b20/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:21:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\\n../2860-7c284b20/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:54:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\\n../2860-7c284b20/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\\n../2860-7c284b20/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\\n../2860-7c284b20/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\\n../2860-7c284b20/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\\n../2860-7c284b20/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\\n../2860-7c284b20/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\\n../2860-7c284b20/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\\n../3995-405a3717/tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/ValidateLibraryStatsTaskTests.java:45:                            \\\"coveredCalls\\\": 1,\\n../3995-405a3717/tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/