k-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/ReadmeBadgeSummarySupportTests.java:384:                        \\\"totalCalls\\\": 2\\n../3995-405a3717/tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/ReadmeBadgeSummarySupportTests.java:392:                        \\\"coveredCalls\\\": 2,\\n../3995-405a3717/tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/ReadmeBadgeSummarySupportTests.java:393:                        \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 1.0,\\n../3995-405a3717/tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/ReadmeBadgeSummarySupportTests.java:394:                        \\\"totalCalls\\\": 2\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:21:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:54:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\\n../3899-1d6f848e/skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/org.apache.camel/spi-annotations/2.16.2/execution-metrics.json:15:        \\\"coverageRatio\\\": 1.0,\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/org.apache.camel/spi-annotations/2.16.2/execution-metrics.json:16:        \\\"coveredCalls\\\": 0,\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/org.apache.camel/spi-annotations/2.16.2/execution-metrics.json:17:        \\\"totalCalls\\\": 0\\n../3995-405a3717/stats/org.